records.addlTxt:
Zoom appearances.  Defendant in custody at Manitowoc County Jail.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge in count 2, resist/obstruct officer. Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge in count 3, disorderly conduct-dvo.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 1.  Motion granted.
On count 3,disorderly conduct-dvo, the court sentences the defendant to the Manitowoc County Jail for sixty (60) days, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately.
The parties are to determine credit by the end of the week.
DNA sample ordered.
$380.00 court costs imposed and to be paid as a condition of probation on count 2 of this case.
On count 2, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
3)	Pay court costs (including court costs from count 3);
4)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5)	submit to DNA sample;
6)	have no assaultive contact with the victims; J.M.R., DOB: 01-26-1970 and M.A.D., DOB: 06-11-1989;
7)	undergo a mental health assessment and follow through;
8)	undergo a domestic violence assessment and follow through.
Any credit is to be determined by the parties by the end of the week.
Minutes.
